START: Define Variables and Initial Weights
│
├── Set Variable A (e.g., A = 10)
│
├── Set Variable B (e.g., B = 20)
│
├── Assign Initial Weight to A (1–100)
│     │
│     ├── Weight A = 50 (Equal Importance)
│     │
│     └── Decision: Increase A's Influence?
│           │
│           ├── YES → Increase Weight A → Adjust Outcome
│           │     ├── New Weight A = 60
│           │     └── Recalculate: Outcome = A[60%> + B[40%>
│           │
│           └── NO → Decrease Weight A → Adjust Outcome
│                 ├── New Weight A = 40
│                 └── Recalculate: Outcome = A[40%> + B[60%>
│
├── Evaluate Resulting Outcome
│     ├── Satisfactory?
│     │     └── YES → Finalize Model
│     └── NO → Continue Iterative Adjustments
│           └── Loop Back to "Assign Weight"
│
└── END: Outcome Optimized Based on Weighted Contributions
